description:
&lt;p&gt;University college London are looking for Specialist Rotational Occupational Therapists to join their team. This is an exciting opportunity to join one of the largest Foundation Trusts in the UK with an international reputation and a tradition of innovation. At UCLH we are committed to delivering top quality care, excellent education and worldwide research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for someone wishing to join an innovative and dynamictherapy team which comprises of Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists and Speech &amp; Language Therapists. We deliver inpatient therapy services to all wards in UCH and the Westmoreland Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and motivated Occupational Therapists with excellent communication skills and an innovative and flexible approach. This role would provide you with an excellent opportunity to consolidate your knowledge and gain new clinical and leadership skills within a supportive, friendly environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The 8 month rotations include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surgery (including Head and Neck Surgery)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inpatient Adult Haematology &amp; Oncology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A&amp;E and AMU&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respiratory Medicine and Infectious Diseases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Care of the Elderly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trauma and Orthopaedics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inpatient Teenage Cancer Trust Unit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a strong commitment to staff development and service improvement and provide regular supervision and in-service training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC Registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 months NHS Experience (Band 5 accepted)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to be concidered for this oppertunity please apply today.&lt;/p&gt;
